How to Configure the TinkerOS Desktop:

# Desktop > Home Icon (lower left) > Preferences > Tinker Board Configuration
   System: Set the tinker board’s name and the administrator’s password.
   Localisation: Fill out local information before connecting to WiFi network.
   Save and restart
   
# Connect to Local WiFi
Desktop > Network icon (lower right) > join a local wifi network

# Update the OS in a terminal window:
Desktop > Home Icon > System Tools > LXTerminal
sudo apt-get update

# Add Support for Installing New Code
sudo apt-get install git
sudo apt-get install cmake
sudo apt-get install libboost-dev libboost-all-dev

# Add Support for Python
sudo apt-get install python-pip python3-pip
sudo apt-get install python-setuptools python3-setuptools
sudo apt-get install python-wheel python3-wheel
sudo apt-get install python-apt
sudo apt-get install python-matplotlib

